I went ahead and rearranged the logic here into something a bit more straight forward. I noticed that you don't handle other response types here which means that future might hang indefinitely if say a 504 occurs. You need a default fallback that completes the future regardless.




        Suggested change











                    if (!result.isFailed() && response.getStatus() == HttpStatus.OK_200) {



